review_comments.body:
style: (1) we don't use ( in closures, (2) we try to use -> here, i.e recommended style to reduce amount of punctuation: 

```
// Adjust RHS keys
val bAdjusted = b.map { case (key, vec) => (key + n1) -> vec }

// Dump a and b together 
....
```

also definitely needs more comments on closures

it would seem to me tests for directory would be unnecessary. 

also recursion would probably be less circumlocutory if it were considered as deleting (any) resource rather than a directory, i.e.  something along the lines 

```
def quietDelete(file:File) {
    for (nested <- file.listFiles) quietDelete(nested)
    try { file.delete }
}
```

I am also not sure if try { } is actually necessary as this stuff will probably not produce an exception but rather returns false in case of failure. I don't remember already. Also i guess listFiles() may produce `null` under some circumstances, also not sure

